steps.instruction:
1. Combine all of the ingredients into a large mixing bowl 
2. Mix and stir everything together to make sticky, rough dough
    - If you have a stand mixer, beat at medium speed with the paddle attachment for 30 to 60 seconds
3. Leave the dough in bowl, covered with plastic wrap
4. Let rise for 1 hour
5. Gently pick up the dough and fold it over on itself several times
6. Cover again
7. Let rise for another hour 
8. Repeat steps 5 through 7 again one more time
9. Place the dough into the fridge and let it rise for 8 hours (up to 48 hours)
10. When you're ready to make the bread, turn the dough out onto a well floured work surface
11. Shape it into a rough ball
12. Leaving it seam side up, cover it and let rest on the work surface for 15 minutes
13. Shape the dough to fit the vessel in which you'll bake it
14. Lt the loaf reach room temp and rise (should take around 1/2 to 3 hours
15. With a rack positioned 2/3 of the way up the oven preheat the oven to 500F
    - Preheat 1 hour before you want to start baking
16. Just before baking, dust the loaf with flour and cut a 1/2" slash into the loaf
17. Cover the baker and its lid and place it into oven
18. Reduce the heat to 450F
19. Bake for 45 minutes
20. Remove the cover and bake for 10 to 15 minutes
21. Remove from oven and transfer the loaf onto a wire rack
22. Allow it to cool completely
